        <body>
            <pb n="1R"/>
            <p rend="align(right)"><placeName>Baltimore</placeName>
                <date>Dec 25. 1848</date>,</p>
            <p>Dear <addressee>Isaac</addressee></p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">I address you a few lines to inform you, that<lb/> I have removed to
                this place. I have often thought of writing<lb/> to you, but have put it
                    <sic>of</sic> from time to time__don't think I have<lb/> forgotten
                    <add>you</add> your kindness is always fresh in my memory. I should
                    <add>like</add><lb/> very much to see you. please come if you can only stay but
                a<lb/> short time. I live at the corner of <placeName>Howard and Dover Street<lb/>
                    Number 64</placeName>. I have a very good House Cousin
                    <persName>David</persName> helps me<lb/> to pay my Rent. I had to spend every
                cent I had, to pay<lb/> the Freight on my things if you could aid me a little<lb/>
                at present you would confer <sic>a on</sic> me, which could never be<lb/> forgotten.
                I have not been able to procure my winter wood<lb/> and coal as yet. I have a few
                customers who buy my Bitters<lb/> and seem much pleased with them which brings me in
                a little.<lb/> I am obliged to be very Economical. I have no <hi rend="underline"
                    >Servant</hi>. I do all<lb/> my own work and attend to my Bitters also. Times
                were<lb/> Remarkably dull in <placeName>Richmond</placeName> when I left_they are
                trying<lb/> to do away the sale of Ardent spirits altogether Temperance<lb/>
                Meetings are held nearly every Night in the Week. That<lb/> has <add>me</add>
                injured considerably in the sale of my Bitters but I Trust<lb/> in God Times may be
                better here. I saw Cousin <persName>David</persName><lb/> a few Days ago he was
                complaining of <sic>Rhumatism</sic>. When I<lb/> see you I shall have a great deal
                to tell you, you know <persName>Isaac</persName><lb/> I can tell you any thing
                whenever you intend to come let<lb/> me know a few Days before. I have to be out a
                good deal</p>
            <pb n="1V"/>
            <p>I should like to be at home when you do come. Farewell<lb/> Dear
                    <persName>Isaac</persName> may every Blessing that this life affords be<lb/> be
                yours is the sincere wish of your Friend</p>
            <p rend="indent(7)">
                <persName role="author">Reinah</persName>
            </p>
            <p>please write to me in a Day or Two</p>
            <pb n="2R"/>
            <p rend="align(center)">
                <addressee>Rev Isaac Leeser</addressee>
            </p>
            <p rend="align(center)">
                <placeName>P<hi rend="underline">hila</hi>del<hi rend="underline"
                    >phi</hi>a</placeName>
            </p>
